    "extraction_rules": [
        "1. ROOT ENTITY: Identify the primary company (e.g., Nike) as LegalEntity (ROOT). EVERY OTHER NODE MUST HAVE A PATH TO THIS ROOT.",
        "2. CONTEXTUAL ATTRIBUTES (CRITICAL): For EVERY entity, you MUST include a 'context' or 'role' attribute. Naming the node is not enough. We must know WHY it exists.",
        "3. EXTERNAL ORGANIZATIONS: All external companies (Analyst firms, Banks, Partners, JVs, Competitors) MUST be categorized as LegalEntity.",
        "4. NO ORPHANS / NO ISLANDS (ZERO TOLERANCE): Every single node MUST connect to ROOT directly or indirectly. If no direct relation exists in the text, you MUST infer one (e.g., [Company] -> OPERATES_IN_MARKET -> [Market], [Company] -> STRATEGIC_CONTEXT -> [Geography]). NEVER leave a node floating.",
        "5. HIERARCHIES (MULTI-HOP ENFORCEMENT): Leaders and managers MUST be grouped using the full chain: [Company] -> HAS_MANAGEMENT -> [Management] -> HAS_ROLE -> [Role: CEO] -> HELD_BY -> [Person]. NEVER link Person directly to Company.",
        "6. NO BYPASS (CRITICAL): Never link a Person or Brand directly to a Company if a hierarchical path exists. NO SHORTCUTS ALLOWED.",
        "7. MARKET ANCHORING: Every 'Market' node MUST connect back to the ROOT Subject Company via 'OPERATES_IN_MARKET' or 'PART_OF'. NEVER leave Market nodes floating.",
        "8. SUCCESSION: If one Person replaces another, use [Person A] -> SUCCEEDS -> [Person B].",
        "9. GEOGRAPHY: Region -> Country -> Site hierarchy. Anchor the Company to the Region.",
        "10. ANALYSTS & PARTNERS: External firms (Goldman Sachs) MUST connect to the Subject Company via ANALYST_OF (Firm -> Subject).",
        "11. NO ISLANDS: Every node MUST have at least one incoming or outgoing edge that eventually leads to the ROOT. If missing, create 'Strategic Context' or 'Market Context' nodes.",
        "12. QUANT DATA: All financial metrics belong in the quant_data list of an entity, NOT as separate nodes."
    ]
}